Perform Counts Normalization.

NormalizedCount.Rd

Perform Counts Normalization.

NormalizedCount(
  deobj,
  gtf.file = NULL,
  gene.length.file = NULL,
  norm.type = c("DESeq2", "TMM", "CPM", "RPKM", "TPM")
)

Arguments

deobj

Object created by DESeq2 or edgeR.
gtf.file

Gene annotation file used to get gene length, used if norm.type=="RPKM" or norm.type=="TPM". Default: NULL.
gene.length.file

Gene length file, tab-separated, should contains "Gene" and "Length" columns. Used if norm.type=="RPKM" or norm.type=="TPM". Default: NULL.
norm.type

Normalization method, chosen from DESeq2, TMM, CPM, RPKM, TPM. Default: DESeq2.

Value

Matrix contains normalized counts.

Examples

library(DESeq2)
library(DEbPeak)
count.file <- system.file("extdata", "snon_count.txt", package = "DEbPeak")
meta.file <- system.file("extdata", "snon_meta.txt", package = "DEbPeak")
count.matrix <- read.table(file = count.file, header = TRUE, sep = "\t")
meta.info <- read.table(file = meta.file, header = TRUE)
dds <- DESeq2::DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = count.matrix, colData = meta.info, design = ~condition)

#> Warning: some variables in design formula are characters, converting to factors
keep.genes <- rowSums(DESeq2::counts(dds, normalized = FALSE)) >= 10
dds <- dds[keep.genes, ]
dds$condition <- relevel(dds$condition, ref = "WT")
dds <- DESeq(dds)

#> estimating size factors
#> estimating dispersions
#> gene-wise dispersion estimates
#> mean-dispersion relationship
#> final dispersion estimates
#> fitting model and testing
NormalizedCount(dds, norm.type = "CPM")
